nce >= 0.8\n\nOutput your evaluation as JSON matching the NetworkEvaluation schema.\n", "user_message": "Evaluate this synthesis network:\n\nTARGET MOLECULE: L-Alanine\nOVERALL STRATEGY: The synthesis network models the prebiotic formation of L-alanine via ten experimentally validated pathways, strictly grounded in the deep literature review. Pathways include Strecker synthesis, Miller-Urey spark discharge, cyanosulfidic chemistry, reductive amination of pyruvate, Bucherer-Bergs reaction, HCN oligomer hydrolysis, Fischer-Tropsch-type synthesis, UV photolysis of interstellar ices, serine/aspartate thermal decarboxylation, and proto-metabolic cycles. Hub molecules\u2014acetaldehyde, pyruvate, HCN oligomers, and \u03b1-aminopropionitrile\u2014connect multiple routes. Environmental interconnection is explicit: hydrothermal, surface, and biochemical settings feed each other. Mineral catalysts are atomically specified in all relevant reactions; wet-dry or ice-eutectic cycles concentrate reactants at critical branch points. The racemic nature of prebiotic alanine is preserved, with homochirality emergence modeled as RNA-mediated selection or CISS-driven amplification.\n\nMOLECULES (15 nodes):\n  - mol_001: CH\u2084 (Methane) [starting]\n  - mol_002: NH\u2083 (Ammonia) [starting]\n  - mol_003: HCN (HCN) [starting/hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_004: CH\u2082O (Formaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_005: CH\u2083CHO (Acetaldehyde) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_006: CH\u2083COCOOH (Pyruvic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_007: CH\u2083CH(NH\u2082)CN (\u03b1-Aminopropionitrile) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_008: C4H4N4 (DAMN) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_009: C5H6N2O2 (5-Methylhydantoin) [intermediate]\n  - mol_010: CH\u2083CH(NH\u2082)CONH\u2082 (Alaninamide) [intermediate]\n  - mol_011: CH\u2083CH(NH\u2082)COOH (L-Alanine) [target]\n  - mol_012: C3H7NO3 (Serine) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_013: C4H7NO4 (Aspartic acid) [hub_intermediate]\n  - mol_014: CO (Carbon monoxide) [starting